 {"id":"asupersync-1qm7d","title":"[Distributed] Define DistributedRegion State Model","description":"# Bead: asupersync-qqw

## [Distributed] Define DistributedRegion State Model

**Status**: Specified
**Priority**: High
**Dependencies**: `src/record/region.rs`, `src/types/symbol.rs`, `src/error.rs`

---

## Overview and Purpose

This bead defines the state machine for distributed region lifecycle management in asupersync. A `DistributedRegion` extends the local `RegionRecord` concept to operate across multiple replicas, providing fault-tolerant structured concurrency with RaptorQ erasure coding for state replication.

### Design Goals

1. **Consistency with local semantics**: Distributed states mirror the local `RegionState` flow while adding distributed-specific states
2. **Partition tolerance**: Region can operate in degraded mode when replicas are unavailable
3. **Recovery support**: Clear transitions for triggering and completing recovery
4. **Cancel-correctness**: All state transitions respect cancellation semantics

### Relationship to Local Regions

```
Local RegionState:       Distributed Extension:
  Open                     Initializing -> Active
  Closing                  Active -> Degraded (optional)
  Draining                 Active -> Recovering (optional)
  Finalizing               Closing
  Closed                   Closed
```

---

## Core Types

### DistributedRegionState

```rust
//! Distributed region state machine.
//!
//! State transitions form a directed graph with well-defined triggers:
//!
//! ```text
//!                    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
//!                    │                                         │
//!                    ▼                                         │
//!  ┌──────────────────────┐                                    │
//!  │     Initializing     │────────────────┐                   │
//!  │  (quorum forming)    │                │                   │
//!  └──────────┬───────────┘                │                   │
//!             │ quorum_reached             │ init_timeout      │
//!             ▼                            │                   │
//!  ┌──────────────────────┐                │                   │
//!  │       Active         │◄───────────────┤                   │
//!  │ (normal operation)   │                │                   │
//!  └──┬───────────────┬───┘                │                   │
//!     │               │                    │                   │
//!     │ replica_lost  │ local_close        │                   │
//!     ▼               │                    │                   │
//!  ┌──────────────────┴───┐                │                   │
//!  │      Degraded        │────────────────┤                   │
//!  │ (below quorum, R/O)  │                │                   │
//!  └──────────┬───────────┘                │                   │
//!             │ recovery_triggered         │                   │
//!             ▼                            │                   │
//!  ┌──────────────────────┐                │                   │
//!  │     Recovering       │────────────────┘                   │
//!  │ (rebuilding state)   │                                    │
//!  └──────────┬───────────┘                                    │
//!             │ recovery_complete / recovery_failed            │
//!             │                                                │
//!             ├────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
//!             │ (back to Active on success)
//!             │
//!             │ close_requested (from any state)
//!             ▼
//!  ┌──────────────────────┐
//!  │       Closing        │
//!  │ (draining + finalize)│
//!  └──────────┬───────────┘
//!             │ all_replicas_closed
//!             ▼
//!  ┌──────────────────────┐
//!  │        Closed        │
//!  │    (terminal)        │
//!  └──────────────────────┘
//! ```

use crate::types::{RegionId, Time};
use core::fmt;

/// The state of a distributed region in its lifecycle.
///
/// Unlike local `RegionState`, this captures distributed-specific phases
/// including initialization quorum, degraded operation, and recovery.
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq, Hash)]
pub enum DistributedRegionState {
    /// Region is forming initial quorum with replicas.
    ///
    /// Entered on creation. Transitions to Active once minimum replicas
    /// acknowledge the region. May timeout to Degraded or fail to Closed.
    Initializing,

    /// Region is operating normally with quorum maintained.
    ///
    /// All operations (spawn, cancel, finalize) propagate to replicas.
    /// Consistency level determines when operations complete.
    Active,

    /// Region is operating below quorum (read-only mode).
    ///
    /// Write operations are rejected. Recovery can be triggered to
    /// restore quorum. May transition to Recovering or Closing.
    Degraded,

    /// Region is recovering state from available replicas.
    ///
    /// Uses RaptorQ decoding to reconstruct region state.
    /// Transitions to Active on success, Closing on unrecoverable failure.
    Recovering,

    /// Region is closing across all replicas.
    ///
    /// Combines local Closing/Draining/Finalizing into a single
    /// distributed close phase. No new work accepted.
    Closing,

    /// Terminal state - region is fully closed on all replicas.
    Closed,
}

impl DistributedRegionState {
    /// Returns true if the region can accept new work (spawns).
    #[must_use]
    pub const fn can_spawn(&self) -> bool {
        matches!(self, Self::Active)
    }

    /// Returns true if the region is in a terminal state.
    #[must_use]
    pub const fn is_terminal(&self) -> bool {
        matches!(self, Self::Closed)
    }

    /// Returns true if the region is in a degraded or recovery state.
    #[must_use]
    pub const fn is_unhealthy(&self) -> bool {
        matches!(self, Self::Degraded | Self::Recovering)
    }

    /// Returns true if the region can process read operations.
    #[must_use]
    pub const fn can_read(&self) -> bool {
        matches!(self, Self::Active | Self::Degraded | Self::Recovering)
    }

    /// Returns true if write operations are allowed.
    #[must_use]
    pub const fn can_write(&self) -> bool {
        matches!(self, Self::Active)
    }

    /// Returns true if the region is closing (includes Closing state).
    #[must_use]
    pub const fn is_closing(&self) -> bool {
        matches!(self, Self::Closing)
    }

    /// Returns the allowed transitions from this state.
    #[must_use]
    pub const fn allowed_transitions(&self) -> &'static [Self] {
        match self {
            Self::Initializing => &[Self::Active, Self::Degraded, Self::Closing],
            Self::Active => &[Self::Degraded, Self::Closing],
            Self::Degraded => &[Self::Recovering, Self::Closing],
            Self::Recovering => &[Self::Active, Self::Closing],
            Self::Closing => &[Self::Closed],
            Self::Closed => &[],
        }
    }

    /// Returns true if transition to `target` is valid.
    #[must_use]
    pub fn can_transition_to(&self, target: Self) -> bool {
        self.allowed_transitions().contains(&target)
    }
}

impl fmt::Display for DistributedRegionState {
    fn fmt(&self, f: &mut fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> fmt::Result {
        let s = match self {
            Self::Initializing => "initializing",
            Self::Active => "active",
            Self::Degraded => "degraded",
            Self::Recovering => "recovering",
            Self::Closing => "closing",
            Self::Closed => "closed",
        };
        write!(f, "{s}")
    }
}
```

### StateTransition

```rust
/// A state transition event with metadata.
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct StateTransition {
    /// Previous state before transition.
    pub from: DistributedRegionState,
    /// New state after transition.
    pub to: DistributedRegionState,
    /// Reason for the transition.
    pub reason: TransitionReason,
    /// Timestamp when transition occurred.
    pub timestamp: Time,
    /// Optional context (e.g., which replica triggered).
    pub context: Option<String>,
}

/// Reasons that can trigger a state transition.
#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq)]
pub enum TransitionReason {
    /// Initial quorum was reached during initialization.
    QuorumReached { replicas: u32, required: u32 },
    /// Initialization timed out before quorum.
    InitTimeout { achieved: u32, required: u32 },
    /// A replica became unavailable.
    ReplicaLost { replica_id: String, remaining: u32 },
    /// Quorum was lost (dropped below threshold).
    QuorumLost { remaining: u32, required: u32 },
    /// Recovery was explicitly triggered.
    RecoveryTriggered { initiator: String },
    /// Recovery completed successfully.
    RecoveryComplete { symbols_used: u32, duration_ms: u64 },
    /// Recovery failed and cannot continue.
    RecoveryFailed { reason: String },
    /// Local region requested close.
    LocalClose,
    /// User/operator requested close.
    UserClose { reason: Option<String> },
    /// Close completed across all replicas.
    CloseComplete,
    /// Cancellation propagated from parent.
    Cancelled { reason: String },
}
```

### DistributedRegionConfig

```rust
/// Configuration for distributed region behavior.
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct DistributedRegionConfig {
    /// Minimum replicas required for quorum (write operations).
    pub min_quorum: u32,
    /// Total number of replicas to maintain.
    pub replication_factor: u32,
    /// Timeout for initial quorum formation.
    pub init_timeout: Duration,
    /// Timeout for recovery operations.
    pub recovery_timeout: Duration,
    /// Whether to allow degraded (read-only) operation.
    pub allow_degraded: bool,
    /// Consistency level for read operations.
    pub read_consistency: ConsistencyLevel,
    /// Consistency level for write operations.
    pub write_consistency: ConsistencyLevel,
    /// Maximum time to wait for replica acknowledgement.
    pub replica_timeout: Duration,
}

/// Consistency level for distributed operations.
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Copy, PartialEq, Eq)]
pub enum ConsistencyLevel {
    /// Operation completes when one replica acknowledges.
    One,
    /// Operation completes when quorum (majority) acknowledges.
    Quorum,
    /// Operation completes when all replicas acknowledge.
    All,
    /// Local only - no replication (for testing).
    Local,
}

impl Default for DistributedRegionConfig {
    fn default() -> Self {
        Self {
            min_quorum: 2,
            replication_factor: 3,
            init_timeout: Duration::from_secs(30),
            recovery_timeout: Duration::from_secs(60),
            allow_degraded: true,
            read_consistency: ConsistencyLevel::One,
            write_consistency: ConsistencyLevel::Quorum,
            replica_timeout: Duration::from_secs(5),
        }
    }
}
